Package ch.lambdaj.function.convert

Interface Summary
Converter<F,T> Specifies how to convert from an object of type F to an object of type T
StringConverter<F> Specifies how to convert from an object of type F to a String
 

Class Summary
AliasedArgumentConverter<F,T> Converts an object in a key/value pair where the value is the one returned by the evaluation of the given argument on the object itself.
ArgumentConverter<F,T> Converts an object in the value returned by the evaluation of the given argument on it.
ConstructorArgumentConverter<F,T> Creates an object of the given Class by invoking its constructor passing to it the values taken from the object to be converted using the given arguments.
ConverterIterator<F,T> An Iterator that converts its items using the given Converter while iterating on them.
DefaultStringConverter Converts an object in its String representation or an empty String for a null object.
ProjectConverter<F> Convert an Object in map of key/value pairs by projecting them using the given projectors
PropertyExtractor<F,T> Converts an Object in the value it has on the name property.
StringLengthConverter Converts a String in an Integer equal to its length.
StringPropertyExtractor<T> Converts an Object in the String representation of the value it has on the name property.
